  "prompt": "Can students leave after MS in direct PhD programs at IIT's?",
  "response": "Yes, students enrolled in direct PhD programs at the Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) can leave the program after completing a Master's (MS) degree, typically if they wish to pursue other opportunities such as employment or further studies. However, the specific policies regarding this can vary between different IITs and even between different departments within the same institute. \n\nStudents who choose to exit after the MS usually need to fulfill certain requirements, which might include completing coursework or a thesis. It is advisable for students to consult their program guidelines or speak with their academic advisor or program coordinator for detailed information specific to their situation.",
